Another improvement to consider but consider using using the boolean variables directly instead of comparing to `true` and `false`. For example, try converting:

```
if ((swich = true) &amp;&amp; (auto = false)) {
    // more code
}
```
 to 

```
if(switch &amp;&amp; !auto){
    // more code
}
```

This will make it much clearer what the purpose of that `if()` statement is.

